The '1996â97 FA Cup' was the 116th season of the world's oldest knockout cup
competition, the Football Association cup or FA Cup. The tournament started in
August 1996 for clubs from non-league football and the competition proper
started in October 1996 for teams from the Premier League and the Football
League. The tournament was won by Chelsea with a 2-0 victory over Middlesbrough
in the final at Wembley stadium.
